BMX-APS Athlete Privacy Policy
Last updated: June 2, 2026

BMX-APS Athlete helps athletes view assigned training, submit wellness and match load data, record nutrition logs, message coaches, and review performance information shared by their coach.

Information We Collect
The app may collect athlete profile information, training assignments, workout completion records, RPE, duration, readiness, sleep, mood, energy, soreness, stress, nutrition notes, meal images, match load details, injury notes, assessment records, and messages exchanged with coaches.

How We Use Information
Information is used to support coaching decisions, monitor athlete readiness, review training load, communicate with athletes, and maintain athlete performance records.

Data Sharing
Athlete data is intended to be shared only with authorized coaches, administrators, and the athlete. Data is not sold.

Data Storage
Data may be stored locally in the app and/or in the connected BMX-APS cloud database configured by the app owner.

Contact
For privacy questions, contact the BMX-APS administrator responsible for your academy or team.

